# Naming Conventions for Terraform Infrastructure Code

## Overview
This document defines naming conventions used across the Terraform codebase to ensure consistency, readability, and maintainability.

## File Naming
- Use lowercase with underscores (snake_case)
- Remove numbered prefixes (❌ 06-Locals.tf → ✅ locals.tf)
- Use descriptive names that indicate content
- Standard files: main.tf, variables.tf, outputs.tf, locals.tf, data.tf

## Security Rule Naming
Format: `{protocol}_{direction}_{source}_{service}`

Examples:
- `tcp_inbound_any_ssh` - TCP inbound from anywhere for SSH
- `udp_outbound_any_weave_net` - UDP outbound for Weave network
- `tcp_inbound_cidr_postgres` - TCP inbound from specific CIDR for PostgreSQL

## Port Dictionary Keys
Use descriptive, lowercase names with underscores:
- ✅ `kube_apiserver` - Kubernetes API Server
- ✅ `kube_controller_manager` - Controller Manager
- ✅ `etcd` - etcd Key-Value Store
- ❌ `k8s_api` - Too abbreviated

## Variables and Locals
- Use snake_case
- Be specific: `kubernetes_ports` not `ports`
- Group related items: `cluster_nodes`, `security_rules_by_group`

## Folder Structure
```text
terraform/ 
├── locals.tf # Central configurVation 
├── variables.tf # Input definitions 
├── main.tf # Primary resources 
├── modules/security/ # Security-specific module 
├── modules/compute/ # Compute resources module 
└── environments/prod/ # Environment-specific configs
```